  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency health services for conflict-affected displaced and host populations in Bria Hospital in the Haute Kotto prefecture of CAR</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will strengthen the ability of Bria Hospital to provide lifesaving services in an area with inter-communal tensions, unpredictable security and potential for displacement. The proposed programme is expected to reduce morbidity and mortality by placing much-needed clinicians in the hospital in collaboration with the Ministry of Health (MoH). The proposed intervention also seeks to balance the need to urgently improve critical health outcomes with longer-term approaches that strengthen the capacity of local health systems and actors to develop basic health services. This support, through trainings and supportive supervision, will help the community and Bria Hospital to confidently manage the CAR transitional health system. CHF funding will be used to reinforce primary and secondary health services at Bria Hospital to complement existing health programming in an area vulnerable to insecurity and to provide displaced populations with healthcare, given the deteriorating security situation due to the movement of suspected LRA factions in the area.</narrative>
  </description>
